  <p><strong>2. Shop consumables: linear, priced in clicks.</strong> Every consumable scales with current income: <code>price = base × income&nbsp;per&nbsp;click</code>. Not exponential at all — deliberately. Coffee always costs about 45 clicks of effort whether a click earns $2 or $2M, so the shop stays relevant at every stage without ever being retuned. And every energy item restores fewer clicks than it costs — Coffee is 45 clicks paid for 30 restored — because the reverse would be a free-money loop of buy, click, rebuy.</p>

  <figure class="post-img chart-fig" id="shop-curve">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 720 430" role="img" aria-labelledby="sc-title sc-desc">
      <title id="sc-title">Idle game shop pricing: click-anchored cost vs a fixed money price as income grows</title>
      <desc id="sc-desc">Log-log line chart of consumable cost measured in clicks of effort, as income per click grows from $1 to $10,000, from the incremental game WinCode 98. A fixed $45 money price starts at 45 clicks and collapses in a straight line to about 0.005 clicks — effectively free. The click-anchored price, base times income per click, stays flat at 45 clicks at every income level, keeping the shop relevant at every progression stage without retuning.</desc>
      {shopGridY.map((g) => (
        <Fragment>
          <line x1="52" y1={g.y} x2="588" y2={g.y} class="grid" />
          <text x="44" y={g.y + 4} text-anchor="end" class="tick">{g.label}</text>
        </Fragment>
      ))}
      {shopTickX.map((t) => (
        <text x={t.x} y="382" text-anchor="middle" class="tick">{t.label}</text>
      ))}
      <line x1="52" y1="360" x2="588" y2="360" class="axis" />
      <text x="320" y="412" text-anchor="middle" class="axis-label">income per click</text>
      <polyline points={fixedPts} class="line-exp" />
      <polyline points={anchoredPts} class="line-curve" />
      <g class="cross" style="opacity:0">
        <line x1="52" y1="20" x2="52" y2="360" class="cross-line" />
        <circle r="4" class="dot-curve" />
        <circle r="4" class="dot-exp" />
      </g>
      <circle cx="588" cy={sy(lg45)} r="4" class="dot-curve" />
      <circle cx="588" cy={sy(lg45 - 4)} r="4" class="dot-exp" />
      <text x="598" y={sy(lg45) - 2} class="end-name">Click-anchored</text>
      <text x="598" y={sy(lg45) + 14} class="end-val">45 clicks</text>
      <text x="598" y={sy(lg45 - 4) - 2} class="end-name">Fixed $45</text>
      <text x="598" y={sy(lg45 - 4) + 14} class="end-val">≈ free</text>
